WEBVTT

00:01.200 --> 00:03.464
Veronica:
THIS IS MY SCHOOL.

00:03.470 --> 00:05.995
IF YOU GO HERE, YOUR PARENTS
ARE EITHER MILLIONAIRES

00:06.000 --> 00:08.230
OR YOUR PARENTS WORK
FOR MILLIONAIRES.

00:08.240 --> 00:12.574
NEPTUNE, CALIFORNIA,
A TOWN WITHOUT A MIDDLE CLASS.

00:12.580 --> 00:14.571
IF YOU'RE IN THE SECOND GROUP,
YOU GET A JOB --

00:14.580 --> 00:17.140
FAST FOOD, MOVIE THEATERS,
MINI-MARTS --

00:17.150 --> 00:18.640
OR YOU COULD BE ME.

00:18.650 --> 00:21.278
MY AFTER-SCHOOL JOB MEANS
TAILING PHILANDERING SPOUSES

00:21.280 --> 00:23.919
OR INVESTIGATING
FALSE INJURY CLAIMS.

00:23.920 --> 00:25.740
WHO'D THAT GUY RAT OUT?

00:25.750 --> 00:26.853
THE BIKERS.

00:26.860 --> 00:28.054
WHY DOESN'T SOMEBODY
CUT HIM DOWN?

00:28.060 --> 00:29.288
YEAH. I'LL DO IT.

00:29.290 --> 00:31.326
I WANT TO BE THE GUY
UP THERE TOMORROW.

00:33.930 --> 00:35.090
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:35.100 --> 00:37.022
ALL RIGHT. SAY CHEESE.
SMILE.

00:37.030 --> 00:40.261
[ CAMERA BEEPS, CLICKS ]

00:41.400 --> 00:42.332
MOVE.

00:42.340 --> 00:43.659
WHO DIED
AND MADE YOU THE --

00:43.670 --> 00:45.308
WHOA!

00:45.310 --> 00:47.301
YOU ARE A FREAK.

00:47.310 --> 00:49.346
YOU'RE NEW HERE, HUH?

00:49.350 --> 00:51.272
WELCOME TO NEPTUNE HIGH.

00:51.280 --> 00:52.838
[ BELL RINGS ]

00:52.850 --> 00:55.114
GO, PIRATES.

00:56.850 --> 01:00.013
THIS IS ADVANCED PLACEMENT.
WE EXPECT MORE.

01:00.020 --> 01:01.885
IT'S CALLED AN "ESSAY ON MAN,"

01:01.890 --> 01:05.849
BUT WHAT POPE'S REALLY TALKING
ABOUT IS FAITH, RIGHT?

01:05.860 --> 01:07.191
ANYBODY?

01:08.300 --> 01:11.394
DID ANYBODY COMPLETE
THE READING?

01:11.400 --> 01:14.790
VERONICA.
VERONICA MARS.

01:14.800 --> 01:15.994
MM-HMM.

01:16.000 --> 01:18.537
CONGRATULATIONS.
YOU'RE MY VOLUNTEER.

01:18.540 --> 01:22.476
POPE. "AN ESSAY ON MAN."
EPISTLE ONE.

01:23.710 --> 01:26.577
"HOPE SPRINGS ETERNAL
IN THE HUMAN BREAST.

01:26.580 --> 01:29.845
"MAN NEVER IS,
BUT ALWAYS TO BE BLEST.

01:29.850 --> 01:33.183
"THE SOUL,
UNEASY AND CONFINED FROM HOME,

01:33.190 --> 01:37.229
RESTS AND EXPATIATES
IN A LIFE TO COME."

01:37.230 --> 01:42.099
AND WHAT DO YOU SUPPOSE
POPE MEANT BY THAT?

01:42.100 --> 01:44.068
LIFE'S A BITCH
UNTIL YOU DIE.

01:44.070 --> 01:44.923
OKAY.

01:44.930 --> 01:46.488
THANK YOU, MS. MARS,

01:46.500 --> 01:49.901
FOR THAT SUCCINCT AND SOMEWHAT
INAPPROPRIATE RESPONSE.

01:49.910 --> 01:51.662
I THINK WHAT POPE'S SAYING

01:51.670 --> 01:55.800
IS THAT THE THING THAT KEEPS US
POWERING THROUGH LIFE'S DEFEATS

01:55.810 --> 01:59.268
IS OUR FAITH IN A BETTER LIFE
YET TO COME.

02:00.250 --> 02:01.774
Veronica:
RANDOM LOCKER SEARCHES.

02:01.780 --> 02:04.647
IT'S THE LATEST TACTIC
THE ADMINISTRATION HAS ADOPTED

02:04.650 --> 02:06.379
IN THEIR LOSING WAR ON DRUGS.

02:06.390 --> 02:08.517
EXCEPT THE SEARCHES AREN'T
REALLY RANDOM.

02:08.520 --> 02:10.124
I KNOW WHEN THEY'RE GONNA HAPPEN

02:10.130 --> 02:11.654
BEFORE VICE-PRINCIPAL CLEMMONS
DOES.

02:11.660 --> 02:14.390
VERONICA MARS.
THIS SHOULD BE GOOD.

02:14.400 --> 02:17.198
VERONICA, WILL YOU PLEASE OPEN
YOUR LOCKER?

02:18.000 --> 02:19.638
[ DOG BARKING ]

02:19.640 --> 02:21.528
BUSTER.

02:29.610 --> 02:31.669
WOW.

02:31.680 --> 02:34.012
THIS IS A LITTLE EMBARRASSING.

02:46.160 --> 02:48.151
Veronica:
I USED TO SIT THERE.

02:48.160 --> 02:49.866
AT THAT TABLE.

02:49.870 --> 02:53.533
IT'S NOT LIKE MY FAMILY MET THE
MINIMUM NET WORTH REQUIREMENT.

02:53.540 --> 02:56.168
MY DAD DIDN'T OWN HIS
OWN AIRLINE LIKE JOHN ENBAUM'S

02:56.170 --> 02:59.799
OR SERVE AS AMBASSADOR TO
BELGIUM LIKE SHELLY POMEROY'S.

02:59.810 --> 03:01.368
BUT MY DAD USED TO BE
THE SHERIFF,

03:01.380 --> 03:03.871
AND THAT HAD A CERTAIN CACHET.

03:03.880 --> 03:05.199
LET'S BE HONEST, THOUGH.

03:05.210 --> 03:07.974
THE ONLY REASON I WAS ALLOWED
PAST THE VELVET ROPES

03:07.980 --> 03:12.041
WAS DUNCAN KANE, SON OF SOFI'WARE
BILLIONAIRE JAKE KANE.

03:12.560 --> 03:14.755
HE USED TO BE MY BOYFRIEND.

03:20.360 --> 03:25.696
THEN, ONE DAY, WITH NO WARNING,
HE ENDED THINGS.

03:37.910 --> 03:40.470
AND LET'S NOT FORGET
LOGAN ECHOLLS.

03:40.480 --> 03:42.744
HIS DAD MAKES 20 MILLION
A PICTURE.

03:42.750 --> 03:45.548
YOU PROBABLY OWNED
HIS ACTION FIGURE.

03:45.550 --> 03:49.259
EVERY SCHOOL HAS AN OBLIGATORY
PSYCHOTIC JACKASS.

03:49.260 --> 03:50.659
HE'S OURS.

03:52.090 --> 03:53.899
YOU OKAY?

03:53.900 --> 03:54.753
WHAT?

03:55.500 --> 03:58.128
YOU LOOK -- I DON'T KNOW --
HYPNOTIZED.

03:58.130 --> 03:59.666
DID I SAY
YOU COULD SIT HERE?

04:01.900 --> 04:03.231
WAIT A MINUTE.

04:03.240 --> 04:04.969
OF COURSE YOU CAN SIT HERE.

04:04.970 --> 04:06.301
SIT WHEREVER YOU WANT.

04:08.380 --> 04:10.439
T-THAT WAS COOL,
WHAT YOU DID.

04:10.450 --> 04:12.008
CU'I'I'ING ME OFF OF THAT POLE.

04:12.010 --> 04:13.773
WELL --
MY BITCH.

04:13.780 --> 04:16.044
WEREN'T YOU SUPPOSED TO WAIT
FOR ME AT THE FLAGPOLE?

04:16.050 --> 04:18.587
I'M NOT SURE I COULD'VE
MADE THAT ANY CLEARER.

04:21.320 --> 04:23.185
OKAY.
I GET IT.

04:23.190 --> 04:25.488
I -- VERY FUNNY.
YEAH.

04:25.490 --> 04:27.526
I GUESS
WE'RE EVEN NOW, RIGHT?

04:27.530 --> 04:28.849
YOU GET WHAT, BOY?

04:28.860 --> 04:31.021
YOU GET THAT YOU'RE
A DEAD MAN WALKING?

04:31.030 --> 04:32.338
LEAVE HIM ALONE.

04:33.870 --> 04:35.064
SISTER.

04:35.070 --> 04:37.436
THE ONLY TIME I CARE
WHAT A WOMAN HAS TO SAY

04:37.440 --> 04:39.533
IS WHEN SHE'S RIDING
MY BIG OLD HOG.

04:39.540 --> 04:40.939
EVEN THEN,
IT'S NOT SO MUCH WORDS.

04:40.940 --> 04:42.874
JUST A BUNCH OF OOHS AND AAHS,
YOU KNOW?

04:42.880 --> 04:43.778
SO IT'S BIG, HUH?

04:43.780 --> 04:45.668
LEGENDARY.
WELL, LET'S SEE IT.

04:45.680 --> 04:48.808
I MEAN, IF IT'S AS BIG AS YOU
SAY, I'LL BE YOUR GIRLFRIEND.

04:48.820 --> 04:50.811
WE COULD GO TO PROM TOGETHER.

04:50.820 --> 04:52.811
WHAT?
WHAT SEEMS TO BE THE PROBLEM?

04:52.820 --> 04:54.412
I'M ON A SCHEDULE HERE, VATO.

04:54.420 --> 04:56.251
WEEVIL, DON'T LET BLONDIE
TALK TO YOU LIKE THAT.

04:56.260 --> 04:59.024
IT SOUNDS LIKE YOUR BUDDY HERE
WANTS TO SEE IT, TOO.

04:59.030 --> 05:00.327
AW, HELL, I'LL SHOW YOU MINE.

05:00.330 --> 05:01.649
FELIX TOOMBS.

05:01.660 --> 05:03.469
WHAT ON GOD'S GREEN EARTH
IS GOING ON HERE?

05:03.470 --> 05:04.960
ALL RIGHT, GENTLEMEN.
MOVE ALONG.

05:04.970 --> 05:07.996
VERONICA, WHY DOES TROUBLE
FOLLOW YOU AROUND?

05:13.180 --> 05:14.499
SO, WHAT DID YOU DO?

05:15.040 --> 05:16.371
WHAT?

05:16.380 --> 05:18.200
WHY ARE YOU
A DEAD MAN WALKING?

05:18.210 --> 05:19.848
OH, YEAH.

05:19.850 --> 05:21.579
I WORK AT SAC-N-PAC.
[ LAUGHTER ]

05:21.580 --> 05:23.616
LAST NIGHT I WAS WORKING
BY MYSELF,

05:23.620 --> 05:25.986
AND A COUPLE OF THOSE GUYS
CAME IN.

05:25.990 --> 05:28.254
YO, MAN.
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, BRO.
OH, THANKS, MAN.

05:28.260 --> 05:31.024
Wallace: THEY JUST WALKED
RIGHT TO THE BACK OF THE STORE

05:31.030 --> 05:33.328
AND START STUFFING ALL THESE 40$
INTO THEIR POCKETS.

05:33.330 --> 05:35.798
SO I HIT THE SILENT ALARM.

05:41.200 --> 05:43.009
WALLACE.

05:45.610 --> 05:48.329
I GUESS THE DUDE THOUGHT
A $1 BILL WOULD COVER IT.

05:48.340 --> 05:49.841
KEEP THE CHANGE.

05:50.910 --> 05:53.071
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

05:56.520 --> 05:58.147
THAT'S WHEN THE POLICE CAME.

05:58.150 --> 06:00.653
WE DON'T HAVE POLICE HERE.
WE HAVE A SHERIFF'S DEPARTMENT.

06:00.660 --> 06:02.924
[ INDISTINCT VOICES ON RADIO ]

06:02.930 --> 06:04.056
YOU. COME ON.

06:05.330 --> 06:06.957
YO, CHECK IT OUT.
HERE HE COMES.

06:08.700 --> 06:11.225
WHAT'S UP, SNITCH?

06:11.230 --> 06:12.436
COME HERE.

06:13.500 --> 06:15.388
THEY SAY THEY PAID.

06:17.070 --> 06:18.264
WELL, DID THEY?

06:18.270 --> 06:19.237
YEAH.

06:19.240 --> 06:21.538
LIKE I SAID.
[ LAUGHS ]

06:21.540 --> 06:23.576
SHUT UP.

06:24.480 --> 06:26.209
BUT YOU PRESSED THE ALARM
ANYWAY.

06:26.210 --> 06:27.370
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

06:35.890 --> 06:38.450
SACKS, GET 'EM OUT OF HERE.
WE GOT ENOUGH.

06:38.460 --> 06:40.189
COME ON.

06:40.200 --> 06:43.465
[ ENGINES REWING ]

06:43.470 --> 06:46.496
YOU NEED TO GO SEE
THE WIZARD.

06:46.500 --> 06:48.730
AND ASK HIM FOR SOME GUTS.

06:48.740 --> 06:50.503
"GO SEE THE WIZARD"?
HE SAID THAT?

06:50.510 --> 06:52.364
YEAH.
CONGRATULATIONS, SPORT.

06:52.370 --> 06:55.009
IN YOUR SHORT TIME HERE,
YOU'VE MANAGED TO PISS OFF

06:55.010 --> 06:57.399
A MOTORCYCLE GANG
AND THE LOCAL SHERIFF.

06:58.510 --> 07:01.570
[ SLOW ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ]

07:07.920 --> 07:12.459
* YOU AND I,
WE'RE TWO OF A KIND *

07:12.460 --> 07:14.519
HEY, BABY.

07:14.530 --> 07:16.418
IT'S OUR SONG.

07:16.430 --> 07:19.297
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, VERONICA.

07:19.300 --> 07:20.335
ARE YOU SURPRISED?

07:21.540 --> 07:23.007
MOM?

07:23.010 --> 07:24.204
VERONICA.

07:24.210 --> 07:26.872
IT'S ME. CAN YOU GIVE ME --
CAN YOU GIVE ME A HAND?

07:26.880 --> 07:29.030
* ...GET AWAY FROM IT ALL *

07:29.040 --> 07:31.907
* AND BURY MY HEAD IN THE SAND
IF I WANT TO... *

07:31.910 --> 07:35.448
HEY!
WHO'S A GOOD BOY?

07:35.450 --> 07:37.042
WHO'S A BIG BOY?

07:39.960 --> 07:44.727
* YOU WERE LYING WIDE AWAKE
IN THE GARDEN *

07:44.730 --> 07:46.994
* TRYING TO GET OVER
YOUR STARDOM *

07:47.000 --> 07:48.126
GOOD BOY!

07:48.130 --> 07:49.324
[ ENGINE HUMMING ]

07:49.330 --> 07:52.424
* AND I COULD NEVER SEE YOU
DEPART US *

07:52.430 --> 07:56.605
* AND YOU'RE MY BABY *

07:56.610 --> 08:00.068
* YOU'RE JUST ANOTHER GIRL *

08:05.310 --> 08:08.768
* JUST ANOTHER GIRL *

08:16.630 --> 08:18.029
Veronica:
I WAS SHOCKED TO DISCOVER

08:18.030 --> 08:20.225
CELESTE KANE'S CAR
OUTSIDE DAD'S OFFICE.

08:20.230 --> 08:21.720
DUNCAN'S MOM.

08:21.730 --> 08:25.723
SHE HATES ME ALMOST AS MUCH
AS SHE ADORES HER SON.

08:25.730 --> 08:29.188
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

08:37.410 --> 08:39.617
VERONICA MARS.

08:39.620 --> 08:41.417
MY DAD'S WITH A CLIENT.
APPARENTLY.

08:41.420 --> 08:43.888
THAT'S OKAY. I'M HAPPY OUT HERE,
CHATI'ING WITH YOU.

08:43.890 --> 08:45.482
LIKE I SAID,
MY DAD'S WITH A CLIENT.

08:45.490 --> 08:46.957
I HEARD YOU.

08:46.960 --> 08:48.882
YOUR DAD'S OUT TRACKING DOWN
BAIL JUMPERS HALF THE TIME,

08:48.890 --> 08:52.451
YET SOMEHOW ALL THE CASES THAT
COME IN HERE STILL GET HANDLED.

08:52.460 --> 08:53.427
HOW IS THAT?

08:53.430 --> 08:55.091
WE'RE EFFICIENT.

08:55.100 --> 08:56.328
VERY EFFICIENT.

08:56.330 --> 08:59.527
I'M JUST GONNA LEAVE THIS FILE
HERE OPEN ON YOUR DESK.

08:59.530 --> 09:02.260
AND IF YOU DECIDE TO TAKE A LOOK
AT IT, COOL.

09:02.270 --> 09:04.363
ONE OF MY CLIENTS,
LORETTA CANCUN,

09:04.370 --> 09:05.837
DANCES AT THE SEVENTH VEIL.

09:05.840 --> 09:07.831
CLASSY.
THESE ARE MY PEOPLE, V.

09:07.840 --> 09:09.239
SHE WAS BUSTED
FOR VANDALISM --

09:09.240 --> 09:11.208
TAKING A BASEBALL BAT
TO THE WASHING MACHINE

09:11.210 --> 09:13.041
THAT STOLE HER QUARTERS
AT SUDS-N-DUDS.

09:13.050 --> 09:14.779
AND JOHNNIE COCHRAN
WAS BOOKED?

09:14.780 --> 09:16.008
I MAKE NO APOLOGIES.

09:16.020 --> 09:18.045
I LIKE THIS CASE.
IT'S TAWDRY.

09:18.050 --> 09:20.814
MS. CANCUN SAYS THE SEVENTH VEIL
HAS AN INTERESTING WAY

09:20.820 --> 09:22.412
OF KEEPING
THEIR LIQUOR LICENSE

09:22.420 --> 09:25.253
DESPITE THEIR RATHER LAX
I.D. POLICY.

09:25.260 --> 09:26.488
SHE WANTS TO MAKE A DEAL.

09:26.490 --> 09:29.926
IF YOUR DAD HAS TIME,
HE SHOULD LOOK INTO IT.

09:35.070 --> 09:37.538
DON'T GET THE WRONG IDEA,
MR. MARS.

09:37.540 --> 09:39.007
I DON'T LIKE YOU.

09:41.080 --> 09:43.207
I HATE THE FACT
THAT I'M HERE.

09:43.210 --> 09:45.849
BUT I DO KNOW
IF ANYONE WILL BE DOGGED

09:45.850 --> 09:48.444
AND RESOURCEFUL IN THIS MATTER,
IT'LL BE YOU.

09:48.450 --> 09:50.281
DON'T CALL ME AT HOME.

09:50.290 --> 09:51.643
I'LL CALL YOU.

09:51.650 --> 09:53.880
AND I'LL NEED IT RIGHT AWAY.

10:01.160 --> 10:02.559
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

10:02.560 --> 10:03.891
HI.

10:12.470 --> 10:14.006
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

10:14.010 --> 10:15.602
Veronica:
SURE, SHE'S A BITCH.

10:15.610 --> 10:17.271
BUT CAN YOU BLAME HER?

10:17.280 --> 10:20.977
AFI'ER ALL, DAD DID TRY TO SEND
HER HUSBAND TO JAIL FOR LIFE.

10:24.790 --> 10:26.087
HOW'S SCHOOL?

10:26.090 --> 10:27.955
IF YOU THINK
WE'RE GONNA TALK ABOUT SCHOOL

10:27.960 --> 10:30.326
AND NOT THE FACT THAT
CELESTE KANE WAS IN YOUR OFFICE,

10:30.330 --> 10:31.354
YOU'RE DELUDED.

10:31.360 --> 10:32.691
YOU MAKING GOOD GRADES?

10:33.360 --> 10:35.828
KANE'S GOT SOMETHING
ON THE SIDE, DOESN'T HE?

10:35.830 --> 10:37.969
SAY WHAT YOU WANT
ABOUT REAL CHEESE.

10:37.970 --> 10:40.495
I AM A FAN OF THE
ORANGE-POWDER-PACKET STUFF.

10:40.500 --> 10:43.230
MY GRADES ARE FINE, AND I LIKE
THE ORANGE POWDER, TOO.

10:43.240 --> 10:45.458
BUT CAN WE PLEASE TALK ABOUT
MRS. KANE?

10:45.470 --> 10:47.006
SHE THINKS
HE'S SEEING SOMEONE.

10:47.010 --> 10:49.604
LATE NIGHTS, MOTEL MATCHES --
THE USUAL.

10:49.610 --> 10:50.907
SEXUAL APPETITE?

10:54.180 --> 10:56.341
IT'S GONE.
DID YOU TAKE THE CASE?

10:56.350 --> 10:57.715
WE NEED THE MONEY, VERONICA.

10:57.720 --> 10:59.585
GOOD. I WOULD'VE BEEN PISSED
IF YOU HADN'T.

10:59.590 --> 11:01.012
I WOULDN'T HAVE CARED
IF YOU WERE.

11:01.020 --> 11:02.612
GIVE ME SOME OF THAT APPLE.

11:02.620 --> 11:04.224
OH, DON'T --
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

11:04.230 --> 11:05.925
MARS INVESTIGATIONS.

11:05.930 --> 11:07.852
MM-HMM.
JUST A SEC.

11:08.760 --> 11:10.125
IT'S AN DY.

11:10.130 --> 11:11.722
KEITH MARS.

11:12.630 --> 11:14.564
HOW LONG AGO?

11:14.570 --> 11:15.764
WHAT'S HE DRIVING?

11:17.310 --> 11:19.005
I'LL GET THE 7:30
OUT OF SAN DIEGO

11:19.010 --> 11:20.875
AND MEET YOU BY THE THING
BY THE FOUNTAIN.

11:20.880 --> 11:22.472
GOOD WORK.
THAN KS.

11:22.480 --> 11:25.404
MY GUY'S ON THE MOVE.
ANDY PICKED HIM UP IN EL PASO.

11:25.410 --> 11:27.742
ANOTHER DAY AND HE'LL PROBABLY
TRY TO CROSS THE BORDER.

11:27.750 --> 11:29.547
I'VE GOT TO HEAD OUT.
YOU GO.

11:29.550 --> 11:32.758
I'LL HAVE THE FLIGHT BOOKED BY
THE TIME YOU GET TO THE AIRPORT.

11:32.760 --> 11:34.489
DO YOU WANT A RENTAL CAR
IN TEXAS?

11:34.490 --> 11:36.151
YEAH.
NOTHING FANCY THIS TIME.

11:36.160 --> 11:39.027
A BLAZER IS NOT FANCY.
AND WE CAN BILL IT, ANYWAY.

11:39.900 --> 11:41.891
FINE.
I'LL GET YOU A CROWN VIC.

11:41.900 --> 11:43.162
ONCE A COP --

11:43.170 --> 11:45.365
DON'T DO ANYTHING
ON THE KANE CASE.

11:45.370 --> 11:46.462
OKAY.

11:46.470 --> 11:48.028
GIVEN OUR RELATIONSHIP
WITH THAT FAMILY --

11:48.040 --> 11:49.439
FINE.
I SAID OKAY.

11:49.440 --> 11:52.659
IF ALL GOES WELL,
I'LL BE BACK TOMORROW NIGHT.

11:52.670 --> 11:55.468
AND IF NOT,
THE NIGHT AFI'ER.

11:55.480 --> 11:57.505
I'LL CALL AND I'LL CHECK IN.

11:57.510 --> 11:58.647
YOU ALWAYS DO.

11:58.650 --> 12:00.379
AND, VERONICA?

12:00.380 --> 12:01.517
YES?

12:01.520 --> 12:05.240
WHEN YOU GO AFTER JAKE KANE,
YOU TAKE BACKUP.

12:05.250 --> 12:06.387
I ALWAYS DO.

12:06.390 --> 12:07.516
[ SNORTS ]

12:08.720 --> 12:12.053
Veronica: BY THE TIME
DAD'S PLANE LANDED IN EL PASO,

12:12.060 --> 12:13.948
I'D ALREADY PICKED UP JAKE KANE
AT HIS HOUSE

12:13.960 --> 12:16.520
AND FOLLOWED HIM TO HIS OFFICE.

12:16.530 --> 12:20.239
STREAMING VIDEO WAS INVENTED AND
PERFECT ED HERE AT KANE SOFI'WARE.

12:20.740 --> 12:25.336
THE DAY THE COMPANY WENT PUBLIC,
JAKE KANE MADE $1 BILLION.

12:25.340 --> 12:27.205
EVERYONE WHO WORKED FOR HIM,
IN FACT,

12:27.210 --> 12:30.668
RIGHT DOWN TO THE SECRETARIAL
POOL, BECAME MILLIONAIRES.

12:30.680 --> 12:32.238
HE'S BELOVED HERE.

12:32.250 --> 12:35.242
HALF THE PEOPLE IN THIS TOWN OWE
THEIR FORTUNES TO HIM.

12:35.250 --> 12:37.343
AND I KNEW THE FAMILY WELL.

12:37.350 --> 12:40.080
JAKE'S SON, DUNCAN,
WAS MY FIRST AND ONLY LOVE.

12:40.090 --> 12:43.253
HIS DAUGHTER, LILLY,
WAS MY BEST FRIEND.

12:43.260 --> 12:44.989
[ UP-TEMPO HIP-HOP PLAYING ]

12:44.990 --> 12:47.424
GOD, LILLY.
I SEE THE PROZAC'S WORKING.

12:47.430 --> 12:49.398
HIGH ON LIFE, VERONICA MARS.

12:49.400 --> 12:52.198
I'VE GOT A SECRET.
A GOOD ONE.

12:52.200 --> 12:54.839
GIRLS, LESS TALK.
MORE SCRUB.

12:54.840 --> 12:56.296
LATER.

12:57.410 --> 13:00.174
Veronica: THOSE WERE THE LAST
WORDS LILLY AND I EVER SHARED.

13:00.180 --> 13:03.843
THAT NIGHT, DRIVING HOME
FROM PICKING UP DINNER WITH DAD,

13:03.850 --> 13:05.977
A CALL CAME IN OVER THE RADIO.

13:05.980 --> 13:07.447
ALL THE DISPATCHER SAID

13:07.450 --> 13:10.283
WAS THAT THERE WAS A DISTURBANCE
AT THE KANE ESTATE.

13:10.290 --> 13:13.350
[ SIREN WAILING ]

13:13.360 --> 13:16.511
DAD GAVE ME SPECIFIC
INSTRUCTIONS TO STAY IN THE CAR.

13:16.520 --> 13:17.919
BUT THE MOMENT I SAW DUNCAN,

13:17.930 --> 13:20.854
I KNEW THAT THIS WAS MORE
THAN A DISTURBANCE.

13:27.800 --> 13:29.358
WHAT HAPPENED?

13:30.940 --> 13:32.976
DUNCAN, WHAT HAPPENED?

13:34.840 --> 13:36.478
WHERE'S LILLY?

13:39.310 --> 13:43.440
BUT EVERYONE KNOWS THIS STORY.
THE MURDER OF LILLY KANE.

13:43.450 --> 13:46.044
IT WAS ON THE COVER
OF PEOPLE MAGAZINE.

13:46.050 --> 13:47.711
IT MADE "ENTERTAINMENT TONIGHT."

13:47.720 --> 13:50.518
THE TOWN FLOODED
WITH JOURNALISTS.

13:50.530 --> 13:52.521
[ CELESTE SOBBING ]

13:54.330 --> 13:57.367
DUNCAN, TALK TO ME.
PLEASE.

14:02.240 --> 14:04.902
AND EVERYONE REMEMBERS
READING ABOUT

14:04.910 --> 14:06.309
THE BUNGLING LOCAL SHERIFF.

14:06.310 --> 14:09.006
THE ONE WHO WENT AFTER
THE WRONG MAN.

14:13.450 --> 14:15.077
OH, MY GOD.

14:15.080 --> 14:17.583
THAT BUNGLING SHERIFF
WAS MY DAD.

14:17.590 --> 14:19.911
[ SOBS ]

14:27.200 --> 14:29.623
BUT IF MY DAD WASN'T RIGHT
ABOUT JAKE KANE THEN,

14:29.630 --> 14:32.963
IT LOOKS LIKE MRS. KANE IS RIGHT
ABOUT HIM NOW.

14:32.970 --> 14:34.892
NOT A LOT OF HIGH-POWERED
BUSINESS MEETINGS

14:34.900 --> 14:37.664
TAKING PLACE AT THE CAMELOT
AT 1:00 IN THE MORNING.

14:37.670 --> 14:39.331
[ SIREN WAILING ]

14:39.340 --> 14:41.672
THEY SAY THE DIVORCE RATE
IS TWICE AS HIGH

14:41.680 --> 14:43.841
FOR PARENTS WHO LOSE A CHILD.

14:43.850 --> 14:46.000
"LOSE A CHILD."

14:46.010 --> 14:48.410
NOW, THERE'S A EUPHEMISM
FOR YOU.

14:49.680 --> 14:52.342
THAT HARDLY TAKES INTO ACCOUNT
THE WAY SHE WAS FOUND.

14:52.350 --> 14:55.057
WHAT? YOU GUYS FIND A WAY
TO UNLOCK THE PORN?

14:55.060 --> 14:56.482
IT'S THE LILLY KANE VIDEO.

14:56.490 --> 14:58.549
HOW DO YOU THINK
THAT FAMILY FEELS?

15:00.000 --> 15:02.093
SIX WEEKS
AFI'ER LILLY KANE'S DEATH,

15:02.100 --> 15:04.068
SOMEONE FROM THE SHERIFF'S
DEPARTMENT LEAKED

15:04.070 --> 15:05.264
THE CRIME-SCENE VIDEO.

15:05.270 --> 15:08.034
WITHIN 24 HOURS,
IT WAS ALL OVER THE NET.

15:08.040 --> 15:10.201
STREAMING VIDEO MADE IT
POSSIBLE.

15:10.210 --> 15:13.668
SOMEONE MADE A FORTUNE
WHILE DAD TOOK THE BLAME.

15:13.680 --> 15:15.170
SO, DOES YOUR, UH,

15:15.180 --> 15:18.308
DOES YOUR DAD STILL THINK
THAT LILLY'S FATHER DID THIS?

15:19.110 --> 15:21.578
THAT'S MY GIRLFRIEND.

15:23.050 --> 15:24.608
YOUR FRIEND.

15:26.790 --> 15:28.610
DUNCAN'S SISTER.

15:28.620 --> 15:31.589
YOUR DAD IS DESTROYING
THE KANE FAMILY.

15:32.360 --> 15:34.419
WHAT'S THE MATTER
WITH YOU PEOPLE, HUH?

15:36.000 --> 15:37.661
WHAT'S THE MATTER WITH YOU?

15:37.670 --> 15:39.797
HE DID IT, LIANNE.
THE MAN IS A LIAR.

15:39.800 --> 15:42.735
MY DAD'S BELIEF THAT JAKE KANE
WAS THE MURDERER

15:42.740 --> 15:44.207
BECAME A MOOT POINT.

15:44.210 --> 15:47.077
AN EMERGENCY RECALL ELECTION
REMOVED HIM FROM OFFICE.

15:47.080 --> 15:48.968
MOM WANTED TO MOVE OUT
OF NEPTUNE.

15:48.980 --> 15:52.507
THE LOSS OF STATUS, THE LOSS
OF INCOME WAS TOO MUCH FOR HER.

15:52.510 --> 15:55.513
WE WERE GONNA MOVE, ALL RIGHT.
WE COULDN'T AFFORD OUR HOUSE.

15:55.520 --> 15:57.886
BUT DAD WASN'T GONNA BE RUN
OUT OF TOWN.

15:57.890 --> 15:59.881
AND NEITHER WAS I.

15:59.890 --> 16:01.414
DAD, COME HERE.

16:01.420 --> 16:03.752
Woman on television: THE NEPTUNE
SHERIFF'S DEPARTMENT...

16:03.760 --> 16:05.250
HEY, I'M SORRY, HONEY.

16:05.260 --> 16:07.353
ME AND YOUR MOM,
WE'RE GONNA WORK THIS OUT.

16:07.360 --> 16:08.759
...APPREHENDED ABEL KOONITZ,

16:08.760 --> 16:11.797
A DISGRUNTLED
FORMER KANE SOFI'WARE EMPLOYEE.

16:11.800 --> 16:13.358
KOONITZ, A SOFTWARE DESIGNER,

16:13.370 --> 16:15.565
WAS FIRED
DURING THE DEVELOPMENT STAGE

16:15.570 --> 16:18.130
OF KANE SOFTWARE'S
STREAMING-VIDEO PROJECT.

16:18.140 --> 16:20.438
SHOES AND A BACKPACK BELONGING
TO THE DECEASED

16:20.440 --> 16:23.898
WERE DISCOVERED ON KOONITZ'S
HOUSEBOAT BY SHERIFF DON LAMB,

16:23.910 --> 16:24.899
WHO SAID --

16:24.910 --> 16:27.117
[ TELEVISION CLICKS ]

16:33.620 --> 16:36.350
[ SIREN WAILING ]

16:37.890 --> 16:39.323
[ ENGINES REWING ]

16:49.940 --> 16:52.329
WELL, THIS CAN'T BE GOOD.

17:02.020 --> 17:04.284
CAR TROUBLE, MISS?

17:04.790 --> 17:06.041
YEAH, AS A MATTER OF FACT.

17:06.050 --> 17:08.018
I THINK IT MIGHT BE
A LOOSE BELT.

17:08.020 --> 17:09.419
BUT IF YOU WOULDN'T MIND
CHECKING --

17:09.420 --> 17:11.081
HEY, WEEVIL,
WHO GETS THE FIRST --

17:11.090 --> 17:12.318
[ SNARLING ]
GET HIM OFF ME!

17:12.330 --> 17:15.026
GET HIM OFF ME!
GET HIM OFF ME!

17:15.030 --> 17:16.520
[ SNARLS ]

17:16.530 --> 17:18.964
GIRL, YOU BEST CALL OFF
YOUR DOG!

17:18.970 --> 17:20.733
[ GRUNTS ]

17:21.600 --> 17:23.431
BACKUP, CHILL.

17:24.470 --> 17:26.609
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.
WE'LL CALL IT A DRAW.

17:26.610 --> 17:28.669
BABY, COME ON.
IT'S TOO LATE FOR THAT.

17:28.680 --> 17:29.533
HERE'S THE DEAL.

17:29.540 --> 17:31.747
LEAVE THAT KID ALONE
FOR A WEEK,

17:31.750 --> 17:33.308
AND I'LL MAKE SURE
YOUR BOYS WALK.

17:33.320 --> 17:35.811
WHY YOU CARE SO MUCH
FOR THAT SKINNY NEGRO, ANYWAY?

17:35.820 --> 17:37.310
THINGS I HEARD ABOUT YOU,

17:37.320 --> 17:39.083
HE MUST REALLY LAY THE PIPE
RIGHT, HUH?

17:39.090 --> 17:40.409
YEAH. THAT'S IT.

17:42.460 --> 17:44.348
ALL RIGHT. FELIX.
WE GET IT.

17:44.360 --> 17:45.588
YOU'RE A BADASS, OKAY?

17:45.590 --> 17:47.228
AND FOR ONCE,
DON'T BE STUPID.

17:47.230 --> 17:49.027
NOT BAD ADVICE.

17:49.030 --> 17:51.089
ALL RIGHT.
ONE WEEK.

17:51.100 --> 17:54.433
AFTER THAT, WE COME FOR YOU,
YOUR BOY,

17:54.440 --> 17:56.192
AND YOUR LITTLE DOG, TOO.

17:56.200 --> 17:57.633
BACKUP, BE COOL.

17:57.640 --> 17:59.904
YOU GET LONELY OUT HERE,
REMEMBER,

17:59.910 --> 18:01.901
WEEVIL LOVE YOU LONG TIME.

18:01.910 --> 18:03.878
[ ENGINES TURN OVER ]

18:04.780 --> 18:06.771
Veronica: QUITE A REPUTATION
I'VE GOT, HUH?

18:06.780 --> 18:09.317
YOU WANT TO KNOW HOW I LOST
MY VIRGINITY?

18:10.620 --> 18:11.917
SO DO I.

18:11.920 --> 18:15.253
[ MID-TEMPO ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ]

18:18.130 --> 18:20.052
I WENT TO A PARTY
AT SHELLY POMEROY'S

18:20.060 --> 18:21.493
JUST TO SHOW EVERYONE

18:21.500 --> 18:24.799
THEIR WHISPERS AND BACKSTABBING
DIDN'T AFFECT ME.

18:24.800 --> 18:26.267
IT WAS A MISTAKE.

18:41.750 --> 18:43.945
I DON'T KNOW WHO HANDED ME
THE DRINK.

18:43.950 --> 18:45.486
I WISH I DID.

18:45.490 --> 18:49.381
IT TURNS OUT IT WAS YOUR BASIC
RUM, COKE, AND ROOFIE.

18:52.090 --> 18:55.127
[ MUSIC, VOICES FADE ]

20:03.830 --> 20:05.695
I NEVER TOLD MY DAD.

20:05.700 --> 20:08.464
I'M NOT SURE WHAT HE WOULD'VE
DONE WITH THAT INFORMATION.

20:08.470 --> 20:11.200
BUT NO GOOD WOULD'VE COME OF IT.

20:11.210 --> 20:12.962
AND WHAT DOES IT MATTER?

20:12.970 --> 20:14.699
I'M NO LONGER THAT GIRL.

20:18.150 --> 20:20.516
ALL RIGHT, LADY.
LET'S SEE YOU.

20:21.850 --> 20:23.989
[ SHUTTER CLICKING ]

20:33.860 --> 20:35.794
THERE'S VERONICA.

20:35.800 --> 20:37.222
HEY, RONNIE.

20:37.230 --> 20:40.461
HEY, WE'VE DECIDED THAT WE'D
RATHER SURF THAN STUDY TODAY.

20:40.470 --> 20:41.835
YOU WANT TO COME WITH?

20:41.840 --> 20:45.059
DUNCAN WILL PROMISE TO TAKE
HIS SHIRT OFF.

20:45.070 --> 20:47.470
DOES THAT SWEETEN THE POT?

20:47.480 --> 20:49.209
DOES IT MAKE YOU HORNY?

20:49.210 --> 20:50.939
HEY, DK, FLEX FOR YOUR EX.

20:50.950 --> 20:52.474
SHUT UP, LOGAN.

20:52.480 --> 20:54.516
ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT.

20:54.520 --> 20:57.080
HEY. HEY. HEY.

20:57.080 --> 20:59.412
WHAT DO YOU SAY
TO A LITTLE HOOCH, HUH?

20:59.420 --> 21:00.614
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

21:00.620 --> 21:02.656
AREN'T YOU YOUR MOTHER'S
DAUGHTER?

21:02.660 --> 21:05.049
NOW, THERE WAS A WOMAN
WHO COULD DRINK.

21:05.060 --> 21:07.290
WHAT'S SHE UP TO NOWADAYS?
MAYBE SHE'LL JOIN US.

21:07.300 --> 21:08.824
YOU KNOW WHERE SHE IS?

21:08.830 --> 21:09.956
ANY CLUE?

21:09.960 --> 21:11.029
LEAVE HER ALONE, MAN.

21:11.030 --> 21:12.622
OOH.
CHILL PILL, MAN.

21:15.370 --> 21:17.600
TOO BAD.
SHE USED TO BE FUN, MAN.

21:17.610 --> 21:18.269
BYE.

21:18.270 --> 21:19.828
[ TIRES SQUEAL ]

21:19.840 --> 21:22.604
Veronica: IT'S BEEN EIGHT MONTHS
SINCE I'VE SEEN MY MOTHER.

21:25.050 --> 21:28.975
A MONTH AFTER DAD LOST HIS JOB,
MOM SPLIT FOR GOOD.

21:28.980 --> 21:31.983
ALL SHE LEFT ME
WAS A UNICORN MUSIC BOX

21:31.990 --> 21:35.517
AND A NOTE SAYING SHE WOULD BE
BACK FOR ME SOMEDAY.

21:44.030 --> 21:46.760
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

21:52.410 --> 21:55.629
GIRL, YOU SHOULD HEAR
WHAT PEOPLE SAY ABOUT YOU.

21:56.610 --> 21:58.373
THEN WHAT ARE YOU DOING
SITTING HERE?

21:58.380 --> 22:00.473
YOU SAT NEXT TO ME.
THIS IS MY TABLE.

22:00.480 --> 22:02.414
AND WHAT A FINE TABLE IT IS.

22:02.420 --> 22:04.581
WHAT DO YOU SUPPOSE
THIS IS MADE OF?

22:04.590 --> 22:05.818
OAK?

22:05.820 --> 22:07.754
LOOK, IF PEOPLE ARE SAYING
SUCH AWFUL THINGS...

22:07.760 --> 22:09.250
I FIGURE I'VE GOT A CHOICE.

22:09.260 --> 22:11.785
I CAN EITHER GO HANG OUT WITH
THE PUNKS WHO LAUGHED AT ME,

22:11.790 --> 22:14.918
TOOK PICTURES OF ME WHILE I WAS
TAPED TO THAT FLAGPOLE,

22:14.930 --> 22:18.093
OR I CAN HANG OUT WITH THE CHICK
WHO CUT ME DOWN.

22:21.170 --> 22:24.367
SO YOU WANT TO GET THE
P.C.H. BIKE CLUB OFF YOUR ASS?

22:24.370 --> 22:26.565
[ MID-TEMPO HIP-HOP PLAYS ]

22:26.570 --> 22:29.573
THIS IS SO TWISTED.
I LOVE IT.

22:29.580 --> 22:31.445
CAN YOU DO IT?
'CAUSE WE NEED IT FAST.

22:31.450 --> 22:33.645
OH, HELL, YEAH.
FOR YOU, ANYTHING.

22:33.650 --> 22:35.641
I'LL EVEN THROW IN
THE GLAZING GRATIS.

22:35.650 --> 22:38.448
GO TO TOWN.
THANKS, CORNY.

22:40.490 --> 22:42.378
OH, MY GOD.

22:42.390 --> 22:43.982
WHILE CORNY DID HIS THING,

22:43.990 --> 22:46.584
I DOWNLOADED THE PICTURES
FROM THE CAMELOT.

22:46.590 --> 22:48.592
EVERY GIRL'S GOT TO HAVE
A HOBBY.

22:48.600 --> 22:50.693
PHOTOGRAPHY'S MINE.

22:50.700 --> 22:54.363
* WE WERE JUST STANDING THERE
MINDING OUR OWN *

22:54.370 --> 22:55.894
* WE WENT ON AND ON *

22:55.900 --> 22:57.606
* WE ALL SMILE, WE ALL SING *

22:57.610 --> 23:01.706
* THE WEAK BECOME HEROES
AND THE STARS ALIGN *

23:01.710 --> 23:02.734
* WE ALL SING *

23:02.740 --> 23:04.879
* WE ALL SING -- SING *

23:04.880 --> 23:07.269
* THE NIGHT SLOWLY FADES
AND GOES SLOW MOTION *

23:07.280 --> 23:10.215
* ALL THE COMMOTION BECOMES
FLOATING EMOTIONS *

23:10.220 --> 23:12.211
* SAME PIANO LOOPS OVER *

23:12.220 --> 23:14.654
* DIZZY NEW HEIGHTS,
BLINDED BY THE LIGHTS *

23:14.660 --> 23:16.252
* THESE PEOPLE ARE FOR LIFE *

23:16.260 --> 23:18.922
* IT'S ALL BACK TO HIS PLACE
AT THE END OF THE NIGHT *

23:18.930 --> 23:20.181
YO.

23:20.190 --> 23:23.591
* WE WERE JUST STANDING THERE
MINDING OUR OWN *

23:23.600 --> 23:24.919
* WE WENT ON AND ON *

23:24.930 --> 23:27.125
* WE ALL SMILE,
WE ALL SING *

23:27.130 --> 23:31.669
* THE WEAK BECOME HEROES
AND THE STARS ALIGN *

23:35.140 --> 23:36.732
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

23:36.740 --> 23:38.173
AND?

23:38.180 --> 23:39.272
WHO'S YOUR DADDY?

23:39.280 --> 23:40.918
I HATE IT WHEN YOU SAY THAT.

23:40.920 --> 23:42.512
YOU KNOW WHAT?
THIS IS IMPORTANT.

23:42.520 --> 23:45.614
YOU REMEMBER THIS --
I USED TO BE COOL.

23:45.620 --> 23:47.315
WHEN?
'77.

23:47.320 --> 23:48.582
TRANS AM.

23:48.590 --> 23:50.524
BLUE OYSTER CULT
IN THE EIGHT-TRACK.

23:50.530 --> 23:53.021
A FOXY, STACKED BLONDE
RIDING SHOTGUN.

23:53.030 --> 23:54.622
RACING FOR PINK SLIPS.

23:55.500 --> 23:56.751
NOW, WAIT A MINUTE.

23:56.760 --> 23:58.227
I'M THINKING OF
A SPRINGSTEEN SONG.

23:58.230 --> 24:00.061
SCRATCH EVERYTHING.
I WAS NEVER COOL.

24:00.070 --> 24:03.164
I DON'T KNOW WHICH BOTHERS
ME MORE -- "FOXY" OR "STACKED."

24:03.170 --> 24:08.301
I NAILED OUR BAIL JUMPER
100 YARDS FROM MXICO.

24:08.310 --> 24:10.039
2,500 BUCKS.

24:10.040 --> 24:11.405
NO SACK DINNERS TONIGHT.

24:11.410 --> 24:16.040
TONIGHT WE EAT LIKE THE LOWER
MIDDLE CLASS TO WHICH WE ASPIRE.

24:16.050 --> 24:17.074
FIRE UP THE HIBACHI!

24:17.080 --> 24:20.140
* BA-DA-DA, BA-DA-DA-DA,
BA-BA *

24:20.150 --> 24:21.481
FOR REAL.
STEAKS?

24:21.490 --> 24:26.826
[ BLUE OYSTER CULT'S
"DON'T FEAR THE REAPER" PLAYS ]

24:29.760 --> 24:32.365
SO JAKE KANE WENT TO
THE CAMELOT LAST NIGHT

24:32.370 --> 24:34.292
AND HOOKED UP
WITH SOME HUSSY.

24:34.300 --> 24:38.703
DIDN'T I SAY SOMETHING ABOUT YOU
NOT GETTING INVOLVED IN THAT?

24:38.710 --> 24:42.532
I REMEMBER YOU SAYING SOMETHING
ABOUT TAKING BACKUP.

24:43.410 --> 24:45.207
YOU GET PICTURES?

24:45.210 --> 24:46.575
NO MONEY SHOT.

24:46.580 --> 24:48.514
THE WOMAN IN QUESTION
NEVER STEPPED FOOT OUTSIDE.

24:48.520 --> 24:50.408
BUT I DID GET PICTURES
OF LICENSE PLATES.

24:50.420 --> 24:52.479
I FIGURED YOU COULD RUN THEM.

24:54.190 --> 24:55.316
LET ME SEE THEM.

24:55.320 --> 24:57.379
* COME ON, BABY *

24:57.390 --> 24:58.982
* DON'T FEAR THE REAPER *

24:58.990 --> 25:00.719
* BABY, TAKE MY HAND *

25:00.730 --> 25:02.595
* DON'T FEAR THE REAPER *

25:02.600 --> 25:03.589
* WE'LL BE ABLE TO FLY *

25:03.600 --> 25:05.261
STAY AWAY FROM JAKE KANE.

25:05.270 --> 25:07.989
I DON'T WANT YOU DOING
ANYTHING ELSE ON THIS CASE.

25:08.000 --> 25:10.764
WE'RE GONNA DROP IT.
I'M GONNA LET HIS WIFE KNOW.

25:10.770 --> 25:13.978
WHAT? WE'RE DROPPING THE CASE?
WHY? WHAT'S WRONG?

25:13.980 --> 25:15.629
WHO IS IT?

25:15.640 --> 25:17.039
WHY DON'T YOU JUST TELL ME?

25:17.040 --> 25:18.940
VERONICA, NO.

25:18.950 --> 25:20.474
IT'S DONE.
IT'S OVER WITH.

25:20.480 --> 25:22.539
YOU JUST STAY AWAY FROM HIM.

25:31.690 --> 25:34.090
[ MID-TEMPO DANCE MUSIC
PLAYING ]

25:34.100 --> 25:36.751
Veronica: I HAD ANOTHER CASE
TO OCCUPY MY BRAIN.

25:36.760 --> 25:38.864
LORETTA CANCUN SAYS
THE SEVENTH VEIL HAS

25:38.870 --> 25:42.988
AN INTERESTING WAY
OF KEEPING THEIR LIQUOR LICENSE.

25:46.940 --> 25:49.909
THIS WAS PHASE ONE OF MY PLAN
TO SAVE WALLACE.

25:49.910 --> 25:52.708
PHASE TWO WOULD BEGIN
THE NEXT DAY.

25:52.710 --> 25:54.541
LET'S GO.

25:54.550 --> 25:57.269
HEY, FLO JO,
SLOW YOUR ASS DOWN.

26:02.690 --> 26:04.681
THERE YOU GO.

26:05.590 --> 26:07.182
WELL, WHAT'S THIS, LOGAN?

26:07.190 --> 26:10.023
THIS WOULD APPEAR TO BE A DEVICE
THEY USE TO SMOKE MARIJUANA.

26:10.030 --> 26:12.669
THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE.

26:12.670 --> 26:14.194
TO THE OFFICE.

26:14.200 --> 26:17.328
OH, MAN, LOGAN'S BUSTED.
[ LAUGHTER ]

26:17.340 --> 26:19.433
IT WAS YOU?

26:19.440 --> 26:20.634
LISTEN, I KNOW IT WAS YOU.

26:20.640 --> 26:22.301
LOOK, THIS ISN'T OVER, OKAY?

26:23.210 --> 26:25.269
YOU'RE SO CUTE.
I'LL GET YOU FOR THIS.

26:25.280 --> 26:27.373
I WILL.
COME ON.
LET'S GO.

26:27.380 --> 26:29.109
SOLID.

26:29.120 --> 26:30.849
YOU'RE RIGHT.
THAT WAS FUNNY.

26:30.850 --> 26:32.147
MEET ME AT MY CAR
AFTER SCHOOL.

26:32.150 --> 26:34.482
WE'LL SEE IF YOU'VE DONE
YOUR PART.

26:34.490 --> 26:37.482
AFTER SCHOOL I DROVE WALLACE
TO THE SHERIFF'S DEPARTMENT.

26:37.490 --> 26:39.082
THIS WAS PHASE THREE.

26:39.090 --> 26:41.650
WE COULD GET IN A LOT OF TROUBLE
FOR THIS.
GIVE IT HERE.

26:41.660 --> 26:43.321
WAIT.
I'M GONNA DO IT.

26:43.330 --> 26:46.026
I JUST THOUGHT ONE OF US
SHOULD STATE THE OBVIOUS.

26:46.030 --> 26:49.932
[ MID-TEMPO ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ]

26:57.910 --> 26:59.309
I WONDER IF IT WORKED.

26:59.310 --> 27:01.312
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

27:02.280 --> 27:05.113
[ SPEAKING GERMAN ]

27:05.120 --> 27:08.055
[ SIREN WAILING ]

27:13.190 --> 27:14.794
IT WORKED.

27:17.800 --> 27:20.860
[ FIRE EXTINGUISHER HISSING ]

27:22.170 --> 27:24.604
HEY, ADAM.
HEY, EDDIE, IS THE CHIEF AROUND?

27:24.610 --> 27:27.135
WELL, IF IT ISN'T SMOKEY
THE BARELY LEGAL.

27:27.140 --> 27:30.576
I SAW YOU IN ACTION TODAY, BILL.
YOU WERE VERY BRAVE.

27:30.580 --> 27:32.172
DID YOU MAKE THE SWITCH?

27:32.180 --> 27:33.670
FAIT ACCOMPLI.

27:33.680 --> 27:35.238
THANK YOU.

27:35.250 --> 27:37.548
Veronica: PLENTY OF PEOPLE
IN THIS TOWN STILL LOVE DAD.

27:37.550 --> 27:39.347
THAT COMES IN HANDY SOMETIMES.

27:39.350 --> 27:42.148
OTHER TIMES YOU RELY ON
YOUR OWN DEVICES.

27:47.830 --> 27:50.151
[ TELEPHONE DIALING ]

27:51.730 --> 27:53.459
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

27:53.470 --> 27:54.994
Man:
SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO P.D.

27:55.000 --> 27:56.763
[ German accent ]
TONY, IT'S INGA.

27:56.770 --> 27:59.364
UH, GUESS WHAT.
OUR COMPUTERS IS DOWN AGAIN.

27:59.370 --> 28:03.374
INGA, UPGRADE ALREADY.
THIS MUST BE THE TENTH TIME.

28:03.380 --> 28:04.779
PREACH TO THE CHOIR, TONY.

28:04.780 --> 28:06.645
LISTEN, WE HAD A HIT-AND-RUN
LAST NIGHT.

28:06.650 --> 28:09.574
VICTIM GOT THE PLATES,
BUT WE NEED SOMEONE TO RUN THEM.

28:09.580 --> 28:10.717
NO PROBLEM.
HIT ME.

28:10.720 --> 28:17.558
UH, ARIZONA 4 VICTOR GOLF
0,0,0.

28:18.290 --> 28:20.451
WELL, I'LL BE DAMNED.
SOME FAMILIES.

28:20.460 --> 28:21.688
WHAT IS IT?

28:21.700 --> 28:25.261
THAT CAR IS REGISTERED TO ONE
LIANNE MARS.

28:31.510 --> 28:33.705
[ DIAL TONE ]

28:33.710 --> 28:35.177
BORED.

28:35.180 --> 28:37.432
CALL IT A DAY, MAYBE CATCH
A MOVIE OR SOMETHING?

28:38.150 --> 28:41.745
EXPLAIN TO ME AGAIN WHY
WE'RE DROPPING THE KANE CASE.

28:43.250 --> 28:44.387
LOOK.

28:46.250 --> 28:50.710
I, UM, I DID RUN
THOSE PLATES.

28:50.720 --> 28:53.359
AND, UH, IT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.

28:53.360 --> 28:55.692
CORPORATE ESPIONAGE STUFF.

28:56.260 --> 28:59.764
IT'S DANGEROUS.
WE DON'T GET PAID ENOUGH.

28:59.770 --> 29:01.089
SO...

29:05.140 --> 29:06.937
LET'S JUST DROP IT, OKAY?

29:09.310 --> 29:10.868
OKAY.

29:12.150 --> 29:13.139
MOVIE?

29:13.150 --> 29:14.048
CAN'T.

29:14.050 --> 29:15.415
WELL, MAYBE WE CAN RENT
SOMETHING.

29:15.420 --> 29:17.547
WHAT ARE YOU --
WHAT ARE YOU IN THE MOOD FOR?

29:17.550 --> 29:19.939
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

29:20.820 --> 29:22.219
VERONICA.

29:22.220 --> 29:24.427
LITTLE VERONICA,
HOW ARE YOU?

29:24.430 --> 29:25.658
HOW'S YOUR FATHER?

29:25.660 --> 29:27.127
FINE, INGA.
WE'RE BOTH FINE.

29:27.130 --> 29:29.758
I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU SINCE...

29:29.760 --> 29:31.125
SINCE...
BEEN A WHILE.

29:31.130 --> 29:33.018
CAN YOU TELL ME WHERE
THE CORTEZ-NGUYEN PRELIM IS?

29:33.030 --> 29:35.089
COURTROOM THREE.
THAN KS.

29:35.100 --> 29:37.295
Veronica:
THE LAST TIME I WAS HERE?

29:37.300 --> 29:40.201
COME ON, INGA.
THAT'S EASY.

29:45.380 --> 29:48.918
VERONICA.
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?

29:50.120 --> 29:52.418
I NEED TO REPORT A CRIME.

29:54.090 --> 29:56.911
IS THERE ANYONE IN PARTICULAR
YOU'D LIKE ME TO ARREST,

29:56.920 --> 29:58.456
OR SHOULD I JUST ROUND UP
THE SONS

29:58.460 --> 30:00.485
OF THE MOST IMPORTANT FAMILIES
IN TOWN?

30:02.860 --> 30:04.725
I'VE GOT NOT A SHRED OF EVIDENCE
TO WORK WITH,

30:04.730 --> 30:07.858
BUT THAT REALLY DOESN'T MATTER
TO YOUR FAMILY, NOW, DOES IT?

30:07.870 --> 30:09.462
MM.

30:09.470 --> 30:11.938
LOOK AT THIS.

30:11.940 --> 30:13.874
SHE CRIES.

30:15.480 --> 30:17.175
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT,
VERONICA MARS.

30:17.180 --> 30:19.740
WHY DON'T YOU GO SEE
THE WIZARD?

30:19.750 --> 30:21.809
ASK FOR A LITTLE BACKBONE.

30:21.820 --> 30:23.242
WHEN WE FIND THEM,

30:23.250 --> 30:26.117
THEY'VE STILL GOT 20 BOTTLES
STUFFED IN THEIR POCKETS.

30:30.490 --> 30:33.527
THEY SAY THEY BOUGHT THE BEERS,
BUT WE'VE GOT IT ALL ON TAPE.

30:33.530 --> 30:36.124
YOUR HONOR,
CAN WE SHOW THE TAPE?

30:36.130 --> 30:38.963
WHAT YOU'RE GONNA SEE HERE ARE
THE TWO DEFENDANTS OVER THERE.

30:38.970 --> 30:41.097
THEY ENTER, AND...

30:41.100 --> 30:44.035
[ MID-TEMPO DANCE MUSIC
PLAYING ]

30:44.040 --> 30:46.600
WHAT ARE WE SEEING HERE,
SHERIFF?

30:46.610 --> 30:49.033
UH, YOUR HONOR, I...

30:50.110 --> 30:52.908
SHERIFF LAMB,
IS THIS ONE OF YOUR OFFICERS?

30:52.910 --> 30:54.844
IS THIS HOW YOU RUN
YOUR DEPARTMENT?

30:55.980 --> 30:57.982
[ SPECTATORS GASP ]

30:57.990 --> 30:59.787
UH, YOUR HONOR,
IS THIS AN APPROPRIATE TIME

30:59.790 --> 31:02.918
TO ASK FOR A DISMISSAL
IN PEOPLE vs. LORETTA CANCUN?

31:03.860 --> 31:05.259
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

31:05.260 --> 31:08.855
[ UP-TEMPO ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ]

31:08.860 --> 31:10.327
COUNSEL?

31:11.630 --> 31:12.927
[ GAVEL BANGS ]

31:12.930 --> 31:15.398
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

31:21.140 --> 31:24.598
[ ENGINE HUMMING ]

31:39.730 --> 31:41.459
GOT A PRESENT FOR YOU.

31:48.740 --> 31:50.560
I OWE YOU BIG-TIME.

31:50.570 --> 31:52.765
I HAD MY OWN REASONS
FOR DOING IT. TRUST ME.

31:52.770 --> 31:54.431
OH, NO, YOU DON'T.

31:54.440 --> 31:56.431
YOU THINK I'M GONNA LET YOU
GET AWAY WITH THAT?

31:56.440 --> 31:58.579
THAT MIGHT PLAY
WITH THE MASSES.

31:58.580 --> 32:01.242
BUT UNDERNEATH
THAT ANGRY-YOUNG-WOMAN SHELL,

32:01.250 --> 32:03.411
THERE'S A SLIGHTLY LESS ANGRY
YOUNG WOMAN

32:03.420 --> 32:07.242
WHO'S JUST DYING TO BAKE ME
SOMETHING.

32:07.250 --> 32:09.457
YOU'RE A MARSHMALLOW,
VERONICA MARS.

32:09.460 --> 32:11.223
A TWINKIE.

32:13.130 --> 32:15.325
OKAY.
HOW DO I MAKE IT LOOP THE LOOP?

32:17.530 --> 32:19.395
UH, VERONICA?

32:19.400 --> 32:20.389
YEAH?

32:20.400 --> 32:21.992
YOUR CAR.

32:33.210 --> 32:36.145
H EY.
VERONICA MARS.

32:40.050 --> 32:41.881
DO YOU KNOW WHAT
YOUR LITTLE JOKE COST ME?

32:41.890 --> 32:44.688
WELL, I'M PRETTY SURE YOU WON'T
BE GETTING YOUR BONG BACK.

32:47.890 --> 32:49.699
WRONG ANSWER.

32:49.700 --> 32:51.224
WOULD YOU CARE TO GUESS AGAIN?

32:51.230 --> 32:54.267
CLEARLY YOUR SENSE OF HUMOR.

32:55.570 --> 32:57.037
OOH!
NOPE.

32:57.040 --> 32:59.031
YOU'RE USUALLY SO GOOD
AT POP QUIZZES.

32:59.040 --> 33:01.702
THE CORRECT ANSWER IS MY CAR.

33:01.710 --> 33:05.168
THAT'S RIGHT.
MY DADDY TOOK MY T-BIRD AWAY.

33:05.180 --> 33:07.444
AND YOU KNOW
WHAT I WON'T BE HAVING?

33:10.920 --> 33:12.649
FUN, FUN, FUN.

33:12.650 --> 33:15.687
UH, LOGAN.
[ ENGINES REWING ]

33:26.770 --> 33:29.159
WHAT DO WE HAVE HERE?

33:30.540 --> 33:32.804
VANDALISM.
NO, NO, NO.

33:32.810 --> 33:36.007
THE ONLY VANDALISM THAT HAPPENS
IN THIS TOWN GOES THROUGH ME.

33:36.010 --> 33:37.534
WHAT?
YEAH.

33:37.540 --> 33:40.748
LISTEN, MAN.
I DON'T HAVE A PROBLEM WITH YOU.

33:40.750 --> 33:43.514
THAT'S WHERE YOU'RE WRONG.

33:43.520 --> 33:46.387
HEY, YO.
IS THIS O-TOWN ANY GOOD?

33:46.390 --> 33:47.914
I MEAN,
MY LITTLE SISTER LIKES IT,

33:47.920 --> 33:50.559
BUT YOU KNOW, SHE LIKES PONIES
AND JUICE BOXES, TOO.

33:50.560 --> 33:52.687
[ LAUGHTER ]

33:52.690 --> 33:55.750
I SUDDENLY FEEL LIKE I'M IN
A SCENE FROM "THE OUTSIDERS."

33:55.760 --> 33:57.091
BE COOL, SODAPOP.

33:57.100 --> 33:59.227
HEY, THAT'S NOT HIS CAR.
THAT'S MY MOM'S CAR.

33:59.230 --> 34:01.164
SHE CAN BILL ME.

34:05.170 --> 34:06.068
OH, YEAH.

34:06.070 --> 34:08.379
YEAH.
[ LAUGHTER ]

34:11.480 --> 34:13.607
NICE.
JUST A LITTLE
FENDER BENDER.

34:13.610 --> 34:16.716
THAT'S IT.
HEAD FOR THE HILLS.

34:16.720 --> 34:18.745
I'M NOT GONNA SAY IT TWICE.

34:18.750 --> 34:20.286
EXCEPT FOR YOU.

34:20.290 --> 34:22.281
YOU SAY YOU'RE SORRY.

34:22.290 --> 34:24.656
[ CHUCKLES ]
RUB A LAMP.

34:26.930 --> 34:27.988
YEAH, MAN.

34:27.990 --> 34:30.220
I SAID SAY YOU'RE SORRY.

34:31.530 --> 34:34.533
I...

34:34.540 --> 34:35.768
KISS MY ASS.

34:36.340 --> 34:38.535
OOH.
YEAH.

34:40.070 --> 34:41.503
GIVE HIM SOME MORE.

34:41.510 --> 34:43.808
[ LAUGHS ]
NOW...

34:43.810 --> 34:45.038
LET HIM GO.

34:45.050 --> 34:46.938
ARE YOU SURE?
I COULD DO THIS FOR A WHILE.

34:46.950 --> 34:48.542
I DON'T WANT HIS APOLOGY.

34:59.130 --> 35:02.850
SO, THAT, UH, SURVEILLANCE TAPE
JUST...POOF.

35:02.860 --> 35:04.225
THAT'S FORTU NATE.

35:04.230 --> 35:07.165
[ TIRES SQUEAL ]

35:08.100 --> 35:10.568
BYE, GIRLS.
GET OUT OF HERE.

35:11.640 --> 35:13.961
MY UNCLE HAS A BODY SHOP
ON THE HIGHWAY.

35:13.970 --> 35:15.471
IF YOU COME IN, YOU KNOW,

35:15.480 --> 35:18.040
I CAN MAKE SURE YOUR BODY GETS
THE FULL-SERVICE TREATMENT.

35:18.040 --> 35:19.302
OKAY.
NOW YOU APOLOGIZE.

35:19.310 --> 35:21.369
I'M SORRY. WAS THAT TOO DIRTY?
'CAUSE --

35:21.380 --> 35:23.268
NOT TO ME, DORK.
TO HIM.

35:24.150 --> 35:25.583
RIGHT. NO.

35:25.590 --> 35:29.117
FINE. HE HAS THE ONLY COPY
OF THE SAC-N-PAC VIDEO.

35:29.120 --> 35:31.987
WALLACE, LET'S GO DECIDE
WHAT TO DO WITH IT.

35:31.990 --> 35:33.480
OKAY. WAIT. LOOK.

35:33.490 --> 35:35.924
I'M SORRY, MAN, FOR, YOU KNOW,
TAPING YOU TO THE FLAGPOLE.

35:35.930 --> 35:38.125
I'M SORRY.
ALL RIGHT.

35:38.130 --> 35:39.461
CAN I HAVE THE TAPE BACK NOW?

35:41.070 --> 35:42.628
NOPE.

35:42.640 --> 35:44.505
[ LAUGHS ]

35:50.080 --> 35:51.968
* SPEAKING OF THE TRUTH *

35:51.980 --> 35:53.572
* I LIKE TO HEAR THAT
ONCE IN A WHILE... *

35:53.580 --> 35:55.445
Veronica: THIS MORNING,
WHEN I WOKE UP,

35:55.450 --> 35:58.613
I HAD ONE PERSON IN THE WORLD
I COULD COUNT ON.

35:58.620 --> 36:01.350
BUT IF THERE'S SOMETHING
I'VE LEARNED IN THIS BUSINESS,

36:01.360 --> 36:03.419
THE PEOPLE YOU LOVE
LET YOU DOWN.

36:03.420 --> 36:05.627
* UTTER LIES ARE LIKE
BUTTERFLIES *

36:05.630 --> 36:11.057
* THEY JUST BOTH DIE
IN A COUPLE OF DAYS *

36:11.060 --> 36:13.699
* YEAH, SHOW ME ALL YOUR PROOF *

36:13.700 --> 36:16.828
* PUT IT RIGHT IN FRONT
OF MY EYES *

36:16.840 --> 36:23.279
* AND I'LL EVEN LISTEN
TO ALL OF YOUR VANITY *

36:23.280 --> 36:27.376
* UTTER LIES ARE LIKE
BUTTERFLIES *

36:27.380 --> 36:31.077
* THEY JUST BOTH DIE
IN A COUPLE OF DAYS *

36:31.080 --> 36:32.445
DAD DOESN'T THINK I KNOW

36:32.450 --> 36:34.680
WHERE HE KEEPS THE COMBINATION
TO THE SAFE.

36:34.690 --> 36:35.782
HE'S WRONG.

36:35.790 --> 36:39.248
OF COURSE,
I'VE NEVER NEEDED TO USE IT.

36:49.800 --> 36:52.530
OH, MY GOD.
THE LILLY KANE MURDER FILE.

36:53.270 --> 36:54.908
WHAT'S DAD BEEN UP TO?

36:54.910 --> 36:58.869
SOME OF THESE NOTES ARE LESS
THAN A MONTH OLD.

36:58.880 --> 37:00.871
THE CONFESSED KILLER
IS ALREADY ON DEATH ROW,

37:00.880 --> 37:03.815
BUT DAD STILL HASN'T GIVEN UP
ON THE CASE.

37:04.620 --> 37:06.611
MY SURVEILLANCE PHOTO
FROM THE CAMELOT?

37:06.620 --> 37:09.009
WHY IS IT IN
THE LILLY KANE FILE?

37:09.020 --> 37:10.453
WHAT WAS MOM DOING THERE,

37:10.460 --> 37:12.678
AND WHAT BUSINESS DID SHE HAVE
WITH JAKE KANE?

37:12.690 --> 37:16.023
AND THE MILLION-DOLLAR
QUESTION --

37:16.030 --> 37:17.895
WHY DID DAD LIE TO ME?

37:17.900 --> 37:20.323
[ MUSIC BOX PLAYING ]

37:20.330 --> 37:22.195
WHAT ARE YOU DOING BACK HERE?

37:22.200 --> 37:23.394
I SAW THE LIGHT.

37:23.400 --> 37:25.459
I FORGOT A FEW OF MY BOOKS.

37:25.470 --> 37:27.665
LET'S UP AND AT 'EM, ATOM ANT.
IT'S FAMILY FUN NIGHT.

37:27.670 --> 37:31.003
I CALLED OUT TO MAMA LEONE'S.
I RENTED "THE SOUTH PARK MOVIE."

37:31.010 --> 37:31.999
MY FAVORITE.

37:32.010 --> 37:33.238
HEY.

37:33.250 --> 37:34.774
WHO'S YOUR DADDY?

37:35.980 --> 37:37.572
YOU ARE.

37:39.920 --> 37:43.651
UH, I HAVE TO MAKE A STOP.
SO I'LL MEET YOU AT HOME.

37:43.660 --> 37:44.649
OKAY.

37:44.660 --> 37:47.925
BUT HURRY UP.
I WORRY ABOUT YOU.

37:49.930 --> 37:51.397
YEAH, YOU DO.

38:08.250 --> 38:09.911
OKAY.
SO HE LIED TO ME.

38:09.920 --> 38:12.514
BUT I'VE GOT TO BELIEVE
HE HAS HIS REASONS.

38:12.520 --> 38:15.284
HE'S PROBABLY TRYING TO
PROTECT ME.

38:15.290 --> 38:17.053
THAT'S WHAT DADS DO.

38:17.060 --> 38:19.858
STILL, I'VE GOT TOO MANY
QUESTIONS SWIRLING AROUND

38:19.860 --> 38:22.556
IN MY HEAD TO WAIT
UNTIL HE'S WILLING TO SHARE.

38:22.560 --> 38:24.790
THESE QUESTIONS NEED ANSWERS.

38:24.800 --> 38:26.768
THAT'S WHAT I DO.

38:28.440 --> 38:30.897
OKAY.
IT'S A LONG SHOT.

38:30.900 --> 38:32.231
BUT I CAN'T HELP MYSELF.

38:32.240 --> 38:35.539
I USED TO THINK I KNEW
WHAT TORE OUR FAMILY APART.

38:35.540 --> 38:37.428
NOW I'M SURE I DON'T.

38:37.440 --> 38:39.078
BUT I PROMISE THIS.

38:39.080 --> 38:41.002
I WILL FIND OUT
WHAT REALLY HAPPENED,

38:41.010 --> 38:43.911
AND I WILL BRING THIS FAMILY
BACK TOGETHER AGAIN.

38:44.720 --> 38:46.847
I'M SORRY.
IS THAT MUSHY?

38:46.850 --> 38:48.750
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY.

38:48.760 --> 38:56.053
VERONICA MARS --
SHE'S A MARSHMALLOW.

38:57.660 --> 39:00.788
